{
  "stem": "8.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And we started walking towards the house where my aunt used to leave.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And I-- I remember arriving there and going up to the second floor, looking for my aunt.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And of course, she wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And some other people were there, who fortunately told us that my aunt was alive and she went to Miskolc, to live in Miskolc.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "She survived-- not her husband, but her children were with her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we got on the train again, and we went and arrived to Miskolc.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the railroad station, my brother was waiting for us, my brother who disappeared on the first day when the Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I asked him, how did you know that we were coming?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He said, we don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We are at the railroad station every day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everybody who survived went to the railroad station every day to see who would come back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we stayed in Miskolc for awhile with my one uncle, who always-- who also survived, who had a house there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this is where we learned, you know, later on, that my father did not survive.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was so weak, and he refused to eat not kosher meal.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they shot him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother, my younger brother, died just a week before the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He also got weak and sick, and they shot him on the march, on the death march.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I remember crying.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember crying and trying to make peace with that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I don't think I really dealt with it at that time, that they were no longer there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because we kept believing that somehow people will be coming home and then some day they would appear.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
